# Worker (`@triage-ops/worker`)

## Layout

- `src/workers/` — job processors (business logic)
- `src/queues/` — BullMQ queue factories
- `src/lib/github/`, `src/lib/gitlab/` — VCS REST clients (+ MSW tests)
- `src/lib/lock.ts` — Redis locks (`triage-ops:lock:{resource}`)
- `src/index.ts` — register workers, startup recovery

## Adding a queue

1. Constant + payload in `packages/shared-types`
2. Queue factory in `src/queues/`
3. Processor in `src/workers/`
4. Register `Worker` in `src/index.ts`
5. Enqueue helper in `apps/web/lib/queue.ts` if triggered from web

## Patterns

- Acquire per-project lock before mutating project data; release in `finally`.
- VCS HTTP: use existing clients; mock with MSW in `*.test.ts`.
- Processor tests: mock Prisma + external clients; avoid real Redis/VCS in unit tests.
- Production bundle: esbuild in `package.json` build script.

